title: For Sale:  NEW Savage 110BA 338 Lapua with Nightforce NXS Scope and SKB Case
postcontent:
Savage Arms 110 BA .338 Lapua Magnum with Nightforce NXS 5.5-20x50 Riflescope and SKB Weapons Case

SAVAGE 110BA Rifle
Brand new Savage Arms 110 BA bolt-action long-range tactical rifle chambered in .338 Lapua Magnum.  The 110 is part of Savage’s Law Enforcement series and is equipped with the patented AccuStock and AccuTrigger. The AccuStock uses a fiberglass lining within the stock, which wedges the action in the stock (on top of screwing it in) rendering it immobile ensuring the rifle will shoot straight. The barrel is free-floated, so the stock doesn’t interfere with its action. The actual trigger of the 110 requires a very short pull, which is great for a precision rifle, but since it is a tactical rifle, light triggers pose a safety hazard because of accidental discharges. So Savage implemented the AccuTrigger, which is basically a trigger on a trigger. The AccuTrigger prevents accidental discharges by using an internal lever that must be lifted before the firing pin can punch forward. Also, shooters don’t have to switch the safety off after sighting in. The rifle features a 5 round detachable box magazine, aluminum stock and frame, 26” fluted carbon steel barrel with factory muzzle break, and a 3 position picatinny rail system with a 20 MOA scope rail.  The entire rifle is finished in matte black.

Nightforce NXS Riflescope
Mounted to the rifle is a brand new Nightforce NXS 5.5-22x50 ZeroStop Mil Dot C205 riflescope mounted with Nightforce A268 Ultralite 30mm 6 screw rings.  Originally developed for the U.S. military’s extreme long range shooting and hard target interdiction, the Nightforce NXS™ models provide a broad magnification range, four inches of eye relief and 100 MOA of elevation travel. These characteristics, combined with the extreme ruggedness and reliability of every Nightforce riflescope, make them ideal for even the largest calibers. The slim profile of the 5.5-22 x 50 NXS™ makes it easily adaptable to a wide range of mounting systems. Its superb resolution at high magnification opens an entirely new world of extended range shooting for the accomplished marksman; Nightforce shooters are now accurately reaching to 2000 yards and beyond.  Regarding the riflescope mounting rings, when a tough, reliable mounting system is required without adding substantial weight, Nightforce Ultralite rings are the answer. They feature CNC machined 7075- T6 hard anodized aluminum bodies and titanium beta series cross bolts and jaws. This unique construction provides exceptional strength, normally not found in lightweight rings. Testing has proven that this combination is actually stronger than steel.

SKB Weapons Case
Included is a brand new SKB R Series Weapons Case molded in desert tan.  The R Series Weapons Case is roto-molded of HDPE polyethylene for strength and durability. Convenient convoluted bunk bed style foam interior.  Molded in valance with gasketed seal and pressure equalization valve to comply with Military Standards making the case watertight and dust proof. Roller blade style wheels for easy deployment. Injection molded oversized carrying handle and tow handle. Black powder coated stainless steel twist latches with locking hasps that will accommodate customer supplied locks or SKB's new 1SKB-PDL TSA Combination Padlock. Interlocking stacking ribs on the top and bottom for stability when stacked.  It comes with SKB's Dual Protection - the Million Mile Lifetime Guaranty as well as the $1500 Content Coverage if your firearm is damaged by commercial airline travel.

Miscellaneous

title: For Sale:  Military Pistol Lanyards - Russian, Czech, Swedish, and More
postcontent:
I recently dug an old box out of my closet where I've stored all the spare lanyards I've accumulated over the last 38 years. 

There are several types with most be the traditional woven rope style. Most of these rope style lanyards are in excellent to like new condition and some (CZ52 & VZ 61) are still in their original packaging. Price on any of the woven rope style is $5 each, two for $8, or three for $10 which includes shipping in a first class envelope via the post office directly to your door.

There are also several leather strap lanyards that are Russian and were intended for the TT33 & Makarov pistols, but they look historically accurate on most pistols of the same era. These are all original pieces that were issued so they do show that wear. I'd consider all of them to be in good condition with soft leather and no rips or tears. These are $7 each postage paid.

Next I have two real and original Russian lanyards for the 7.62x38 Nagant revolver. They are in excellent issued condition. You can find modern reproductions on eBay and other sites but it's difficult to find an original anymore. $15 each including postage.

Finally I have several rare Swedish made leather rope lanyards in unissued condition. They were originally produced for the Swedish LAHTI pistols, but I've used them on other pistols of the same general time period and they look great. They also pair up very nicely with many of the WWI & WWII flare pistols out there today. Price is $10 each including postage.

I accept Paypal.

Thanks for looking

title: Want To Buy:  SKS rifle
location: Elizabeth City, NC, North Carolina, United States
postcontent:
Hello, 

I am looking to purchase two SKS rifles if available but offers of just a single rifle are more then welcome. I will consider all manufacturers, as they seemingly all had their good and bad production runs, and the individual rifle quality is much more important to me then the average of that production year. I will not consider rifles of what I consider extensive historic value (Extremely low serial numbers, those with "trench art", extensive stamps and markings suggesting a long service history, etc) because, while I do intend on adding it to a well maintained collection, I intend to shoot this rifle without fear that I am hurting a special piece. 

Moderate to strong rifling is a MUST and I will prefer those with chrome bores. The rifle does not have to function but I will consider these offers on an individual basis with great scrutiny. Ideally the rifle will still have it's wood stock and bayonet. I will consider offers of rifles that have been modified ONLY if the parts to restore the weapon to its original layout are included. Having said that, the wood stock can be extensively damaged (for example: cracked in half is OK). Honestly, any modifications will not add much value to the weapon for me as they will more then likely be undone. The serial numbers do not have to match, though this is preferred. 

I am willing to pay a fair price, but please understand that the more money you ask for, the more pictures and information about the gun I will ask for. 

Feel free to call or text anytime, 252 three one two 73 seven eight. Please include your name, make, and year of the rifle. 

-Pat
